cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.AL, cs.CG 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with wireless scheduling and power control in the context of interference in wireless networks. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper mentions the signal-to-interference-plus-noise (SINR) constraints, which is a concept from information theory. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes an algorithm for scheduling and power control. 
- cs.AL (Algorithms) is also relevant for the same reason as cs.DS. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is less likely but still possible as the paper generalizes the setting from the standard 2-dimensional Euclidean plane to doubling metrics, which is a concept from computational geometry.
